Build Instructions for has_composite_shapes.cpp
==============================================

1. Install Dependencies
------------------------
Install the DjVuLibre development package:

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install libdjvulibre-dev
```

2. Clone the Repository
------------------------
```bash
git clone https://github.com/jsbien/labelshapes.git
cd labelshapes
```

3. Compile the Tool
---------------------
Use `g++` and link to DjVuLibre:

```bash
g++ -o has_composite_shapes has_composite_shapes.cpp `pkg-config --cflags --libs ddjvuapi`
```

If `pkg-config` fails, use:

```bash
g++ -o has_composite_shapes has_composite_shapes.cpp -ldjvulibre
```

4. Run the Program
-------------------
```bash
./has_composite_shapes yourfile.djvu
```

- It prints each composite shape detected (made of multiple blits).
- Exit code `0`: no composite shapes.
- Exit code `1`: composite shapes found.